 work in the quintessentially "modern" industry of financial services and neoliberal "development" regimes, with their grounding in hierarchies of race, gender, class, and geopolitical positioning.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aBanks and banking, InternationalzUnited States Virgin IslandszSaint Croix. 0aEconomic developmentzUnited States Virgin IslandszSaint Croix. 0aFinancial services industryzUnited States Virgin IslandszSaint Croix. 0aTax havenszUnited States Virgin IslandszSaint Croix. 4aAfrican American Studies : Black Studies. 4aAnthropology and Archaeology : Anthropology. 4aBusiness and Economics : Development. 4aGender and Sexuality : Gender Studies. 4aLatin American, Caribbean, and Latinx Studies : Caribbean Studies. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2021z978311149169140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143848604840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438486048423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438486048/original  a978-3-11-149169-1  SUNY Press eBook Package 2021b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles